
[1]intonation

   INTONA'TION, n. In music, the action of sounding the notes of the scale
   with the voice, or any other given order of musical tones.

   1. The manner of sounding or tuning the notes of a musical scale.

   2. In speaking, the modulation of the voice in expression.
